y"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emaxillary artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a terminal branch of the external carotid artery, the other being the superficial temporal artery. It supplies the nose, paranasal sinuses, palate, and teeth (deep structures of the face).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emiddle meningeal artery\u003C/strong\u003E branches off the maxillary artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Evertebral artery\u003C/strong\u003E arises from the subclavian artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eophthalmic artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a branch of the internal carotid artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeep temporal artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a branch of the maxillary artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe eight major branches of the external carotid artery are demonstrated in the diagram below.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The external carotid artery has eight major branches","The terminal branches of the external carotid artery are the superficial temporal and maxillary arteries.","The external carotid artery supplies blood to most structures of the head and neck external to the cranial cavity."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cExternal Carotid Artery\u201d by Mikael H\u00e4ggstr\u00f6m is under\u00a0Public Domain. \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:External_carotid_artery.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63899"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17608"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21343"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21343"